VALUES
(40, 13, 27, 45, 16, 17, 17, 'didst not thou sow good seed', 'Divisions and Tares in the Field', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognizing harmful elements within a community. In Matthew, the servants question the presence of tares among the good seed, paralleling Romans'' call to mark those causing divisions contrary to sound doctrine.', 'theme', 0.356, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 27, 47, 6, 1, 1, 'good seed in thy field', 'Grace and Good Seed Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving what is good, as the servants question the presence of tares despite good seed being sown. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing and acting upon the good that God provides.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 27, 47, 5, 18, 20, NULL, 'Reconciliation and Good Seed', 'This connection highlights the theme of reconciliation in both passages. The servants question the presence of tares, paralleling the need for reconciliation in 2 Corinthians, where God reconciles the world to Himself.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 27, 46, 12, 28, 29, NULL, 'Role of Good and Bad in Community', 'This connection highlights the presence of both good and bad elements within a community. In Matthew, the question of tares among good seed reflects concerns about purity, while 1 Corinthians discusses the diversity of roles within the church, suggesting a mix of gifts and functions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 27, 46, 16, 10, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Good Seed and Work', 'This connection highlights the theme of diligent work in the face of challenges. In Matthew, the question of tares suggests concern over the purity of the harvest, while in 1 Corinthians, Timothy''s work is encouraged despite potential fears.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 27, 48, 3, 1, 3, 'good seed in thy field', 'Connection of Spiritual Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the source of spiritual growth. In Matthew, the question of tares highlights the need for discernment in what is sown, while Galatians questions the reliance on the flesh versus the Spirit for spiritual maturity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 27, 49, 4, 11, 12, 'good seed', 'Connection of Good Seed and Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth and development within the community of believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of nurturing good elements, whether through good seed in the field or through the roles of ministry for the edifying of the body of Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 28, 46, 5, 3, 7, 'an enemy hath done this', 'Enemy and Purging Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of dealing with evil within a community. In Matthew, the enemy''s actions lead to a call for discernment, while in 1 Corinthians, Paul addresses the need to purge sin to maintain purity in the church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 28, 42, 9, 49, 54, 'Wilt thou then that we go', 'Response to Opposition', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of responding to opposition. In Matthew, the servants inquire about gathering up the tares, while in Luke, John and James seek to respond to rejection with force. This connection highlights the differing attitudes towards those who oppose or do not follow the group.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 28, 52, 5, 14, 14, 'an enemy hath done this', 'Warning and Support in Community', 'This connection highlights the need for community vigilance and support. In Matthew, the servants are concerned about the enemy''s actions, while in 1 Thessalonians, believers are encouraged to warn and support one another.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 28, 47, 2, 6, 11, NULL, 'Forgiveness and Sorrow Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the need to address wrongdoing and the consequences of inaction. In Matthew, the enemy''s actions lead to a call for action, while in 2 Corinthians, the focus is on forgiveness to prevent overwhelming sorrow. This connection highlights the importance of responding to evil with grace.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 28, 65, 1, 22, 23, 'an enemy hath done this', 'Compassion and Judgment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of responding to evil. In Matthew, the enemy''s actions lead to a need for discernment, while Jude emphasizes the necessity of compassion and urgency in saving others from danger.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 30, 40, 3, 12, 12, NULL, 'Harvest and Purging Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of wheat and the burning of undesirable elements. Matthew 13:30 speaks of gathering wheat into a barn, while Matthew 3:12 mentions gathering wheat into the garner, highlighting a thematic parallel in the imagery of harvest.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 30, 54, 5, 24, 24, 'harvest', 'Judgment and Harvest Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment present in both passages. Matthew 13:30 speaks of a harvest where the wheat and tares are separated, while 1 Timothy 5:24 discusses how some sins are judged beforehand and others follow after, indicating a process of discernment and eventual judgment.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 30, 46, 4, 5, 5, 'the time of harvest', 'Judgment and Revelation at Harvest', 'Both passages emphasize the timing of judgment. Matthew speaks of a harvest where the wheat and tares are separated, while 1 Corinthians highlights the Lord bringing to light hidden things at His coming.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 30, 43, 15, 6, 6, NULL, 'Judgment and Consequences of Non-Abiding', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering and burning of those not aligned with the harvest. This connection highlights the fate of the tares and branches that do not bear fruit.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 30, 40, 13, 39, 43, 'the harvest', 'Harvest and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the harvest as a time of separation between the righteous and the wicked. The SOURCE verse introduces the gathering of tares and wheat, while the TARGET passage elaborates on the role of angels in this judgment at the end of the world.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 30, 42, 3, 17, 17, 'gather the wheat into my barn', 'Harvest and Purging Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of wheat and the burning of undesirable elements. This connection highlights the theme of separation during the harvest, illustrating a process of judgment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 31, 42, 13, 18, 19, 'like to a grain of mustard seed', 'Mustard Seed Parable Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the kingdom of heaven as ''like a grain of mustard seed.'' This connection highlights the growth and significance of the kingdom, illustrating its humble beginnings and eventual expansion.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 31, 40, 17, 20, 20, 'a grain of mustard seed', 'Faith and Growth Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of a grain of mustard seed, illustrating how something small can lead to great outcomes. The first passage highlights the kingdom of heaven''s growth, while the second underscores the power of faith.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 31, 41, 4, 30, 32, 'like to a grain of mustard seed', 'Mustard Seed Parable Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the kingdom of heaven as a mustard seed, illustrating its small beginnings and significant growth. This connection highlights the transformative nature of the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 31, 42, 17, 6, 6, 'a grain of mustard seed', 'Faith and the Mustard Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of a grain of mustard seed, illustrating the potential for growth and power in faith. The mustard seed serves as a metaphor for both the kingdom of heaven and the faith required to perform miraculous acts.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 31, 40, 13, 24, 24, 'sowed in his field', 'Parables of Sowing Seeds', 'Both passages emphasize the act of sowing in a field, illustrating the growth of the kingdom of heaven. The mustard seed and good seed serve as metaphors for the kingdom''s expansion and potential.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 32, 26, 31, 6, 6, 'birds of the air come and lodge', 'Connection of Growth and Shelter', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of growth leading to shelter for birds. In Matthew, the seed grows into a tree providing lodging for birds, while Ezekiel describes birds nesting in the boughs of a great tree.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 32, 27, 4, 12, 12, 'birds of the air come and lodge', 'Connection of Growth and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of a tree providing shelter and sustenance. The ''birds of the air'' in Matthew and ''fowls of the heaven'' in Daniel highlight the theme of nature''s provision.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 32, 26, 17, 23, 24, 'birds of the air come and lodge', 'Connection of Growth and Shelter', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of growth from small beginnings to great stature, with the imagery of birds finding shelter in the branches. This connection highlights the transformation of the lowly into a place of refuge and abundance.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 32, 44, 21, 20, 20, 'the least of all seeds', 'Growth of Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth, as the mustard seed in Matthew symbolizes the expansion of faith, paralleling the thousands of Jews in Acts who have embraced belief. Both passages emphasize how something small can lead to significant outcomes.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 32, 27, 2, 44, 45, 'greatest among herbs, and becometh a tree', 'Kingdom Growth and Permanence', 'Both passages emphasize the establishment of a kingdom that grows significantly and endures forever. Matthew describes the growth of a small seed into a great tree, while Daniel speaks of a kingdom that shall never be destroyed.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 32, 38, 8, 20, 23, 'greatest among herbs, and becometh a tree', 'Growth and Inclusion of Nations', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth and inclusion, as both passages depict a small beginning leading to a significant expansion. Matthew speaks of a small seed growing into a tree, while Zechariah describes nations coming to seek the Lord, suggesting a similar idea of growth and gathering.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 32, 45, 15, 18, 19, 'greatest among herbs, and becometh a tree', 'Growth and Expansion of Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth, as the mustard seed becomes a tree, paralleling how the gospel spreads and grows among the Gentiles in Romans. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of faith and the resulting community it creates.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
